channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Fani Willis Just Won Her Primary Election—Guess Who Showed Up at Her Victory Party?
Maryland GOP Senate candidate Larry Hogan lines up with Biden on abortion, would codify Roe
item.description: Maryland Republican Senate candidate Larry Hogan says in a new ad he supports laws that would codify Roe v. Wade and protect abortion rights for women at the federal level.

item.title: US Softens Stance on Rafah Op After Jerusalem Addresses Concerns
item.description: The United States has softened its stance on a broader Israeli military operation in Rafah after Jerusalem addressed its humanitarian concerns, a senior Biden administration official said on Tuesday.

item.title: Biden Approval Takes a New Dive and Shows He's Losing Even More Ground
Democrats plan assault on Trump's VP pool, mock 'MAGA Veepstakes': report
item.description: Democrats are making plans to attack former President Trump's VP pick as a radical "ultra-MAGA" Republican as the pool vies for Trump's approval.

item.title: Trump-Backed Fong Wins Special Election for Kevin McCarthy's Seat
item.description: Vince Fong, a California State Assembly member backed by former President Donald Trump, won a special election Tuesday to complete the remainder of the term of deposed former House Speaker Kevin McCarthy, R-Calif., which runs through January.

item.title: Yes, the Mar-a-Lago Raid Was Extraordinary, but the 'Deadly Force' Language in the Ops Order Wasn't
White House accuses GOP of siding 'with fentanyl traffickers' by opposing border bill
item.description: The White House is claiming that the bipartisan border bill, heading the Senate floor later this week, is a vital move to stop the flow of fentanyl across the border.

item.title: Pentagon: Russia Put Weapon into Space on May 16
item.description: Russia last week launched a satellite that U.S. intelligence officials believe to be a weapon capable of inspecting and attacking other satellites, the U.S. Space Command said on Tuesday as the Russian spacecraft trails a U.S. spy satellite in orbit.Russia's Soyuz rocket...

item.title: US: Russia Just Launched Space Weapon Capable of Attacking Our Satellites
Cornel West joins DC reparations protest against Wells Fargo Bank
item.description: Independent presidential candidate Cornel West spoke at a reparations demonstration in front of the Wells Fargo branch on Capitol Hill on Tuesday.

item.title: Senate Dems Brace for Fewer Votes on Border — From Own Side
item.description: Senate Democrats acknowledge they're facing an uphill battle within their own ranks on the bipartisan border bill that leadership plans to bring to the floor later this week, Politico reported Tuesday.

item.title: What Happened Today Shows How Cozy CA Dems and (Some) Republicans Are With Illegal Alien Pedophiles
Biden blasted by experts for repeating 'debunked lie' to Black students at HBCU graduation: 'Factually false'
item.description: President Biden was blasted on social media and by experts after telling Morehouse College graduates that Georgia's voting law doesn't allow voters to drink water in line.

item.title: Incumbent Ga. Justice Pinson Tops Ex-Dem Rep. Barrow
item.description: Incumbent Georgia Supreme Court Justice Andrew Pinson defeated abortion-fueled challenge from John Barrow on Tuesday in nonpartisan court race.
